    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>Feb, 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1882</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I wish that I c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. answer your question, but I cannot.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> The usual cause of the death of worms is a parasitic larva of a Fly, but this c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. not apply especially to asphalt pavement.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Worms are very susceptible to certain poisons, &amp; coal-tar is poisonous to plants for a quite extraordinary length of time, &amp; it may be so to earth-worms.— I have here an uncovered tennis court, consisting of concrete, &amp; my sons tell me that they have often noticed dead &amp; dying worms on the smooth surface; &amp; this makes the whole case still more perplexing.—</p> <p>I am glad that my little book has at all interested you &amp; I remain | Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.2 a parasitic] ‘a’ <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘the’; ‘parasitic’ <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.5 uncovered] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘open’ </note>
            </div>
            
            
                       
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Leng’s letter has not been found.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref>, p. 14, CD had mentioned parasitic fly larvae as a cause of death in worms. Cluster flies (genus <hi rend="italic">Pollenia</hi>) are the principal parasitoids of earthworms.</note>
        </div> 
     
